main event: An unidentified flying object was reported in Odessa, Delaware on February 9, 1967.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 5 minutes and involved a bright light in the sky, The object was described as round, 40-50 feet in diameter, and emitted a bright orange light, The object hovered briefly before accelerating rapidly and disappearing, There were multiple witnesses to the event, including Mr. John Doe and occupants of a nearby farmhouse, The case was classified as unidentified due to a lack of evidence and no logical explanation found during the investigation.
sighted object: a bright round object emitting orange light
witness description: Mr. John Doe and occupants of a nearby farmhouse
